<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="intro-section" id="overview">
<div class="intro-inner">
<div class="intro-left">
<h2>Evaluate the role. Not the person.</h2>
<p>Engage is built on one core principle: a role should be graded based on what the organisation requires it to do — not on the performance, tenure, or attributes of the person currently doing it.</p>
<p>That means the framework focuses on the content and design of the role: the knowledge it requires, the decisions it makes, the people it manages, and the impact it has on the organisation.</p>
<p>The result is a grading outcome that is more consistent, more defensible, and easier to explain to leaders and employees alike.</p>
</div>
<div class="intro-right">
<ul class="principle-list">
<li class="principle-item">
<div class="principle-dot"></div>
<div><strong>Role content, not person attributes</strong><span>Grading reflects what the job requires — not who is in it.</span></div>
</li>
<li class="principle-item">
<div class="principle-dot"></div>
<div><strong>Judgement, not guesswork</strong><span>Structured dimensions create consistency across very different role types.</span></div>
</li>
<li class="principle-item">
<div class="principle-dot"></div>
<div><strong>Transparency over mystery</strong><span>Every judgement is visible. Nothing is hidden from the people involved.</span></div>
</li>
<li class="principle-item">
<div class="principle-dot"></div>
<div><strong>Direct knowledge over paperwork</strong><span>People who understand the role participate. Job descriptions are useful, not essential.</span></div>
</li>
<li class="principle-item">
<div class="principle-dot"></div>
<div><strong>Internal ownership over dependency</strong><span>Designed to be maintained internally after implementation, not to keep consultants in the room forever.</span></div>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<!-- TWO PILLARS -->
<section class="pillars-section" id="two-pillars">
<div class="pillars-inner">
<div class="section-eyebrow">The framework at a glance</div>
<h2>Two pillars. Five grids.</h2>
<p>At the highest level, Engage looks at two things: the skills required for the role, and the organisational context in which the role operates. Together these create a balanced view of role size.</p>
<div class="pillars-grid">
<div class="pillar">
<div class="pillar-head" onclick="togglePillar(this)">
<div class="pillar-icon">I</div>
<div class="pillar-head-text">
<h3>Skills required</h3>
<p>What the role demands of the person in it</p>
</div>
<span class="pillar-chevron" aria-hidden="true">&#9662;</span>
</div>
<div class="pillar-body">
<div class="pillar-dim">
<div class="pillar-dim-label">Technical skills</div>
<div class="pillar-dim-text">The depth and application of knowledge required to perform the role effectively.</div>
</div>
<div class="pillar-dim">
<div class="pillar-dim-label">Managerial skills</div>
<div class="pillar-dim-text">The extent to which the role coordinates work and makes business decisions.</div>
</div>
<div class="pillar-dim">
<div class="pillar-dim-label">Persuasive skills</div>
<div class="pillar-dim-text">The degree to which the role must influence, negotiate, or secure outcomes through others.</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pillar">
<div class="pillar-head" onclick="togglePillar(this)">
<div class="pillar-icon">II</div>
<div class="pillar-head-text">
<h3>Organisational context</h3>
<p>Where the role sits and what it controls</p>
</div>
<span class="pillar-chevron" aria-hidden="true">&#9662;</span>
</div>
<div class="pillar-body">
<div class="pillar-dim">
<div class="pillar-dim-label">Control</div>
<div class="pillar-dim-text">The scale of operational responsibility — staff reporting and sites controlled.</div>
</div>
<div class="pillar-dim">
<div class="pillar-dim-label">Impact</div>
<div class="pillar-dim-text">How significant the role is within the organisation — responsibility and reporting level.</div>
</div>
<div class="pillar-dim">
<div class="pillar-dim-label">Influence <em style="font-size:11px;color:var(--slate);font-style:normal;">(alternate)</em></div>
<div class="pillar-dim-text">Used for flexible or person-related assignments where projection and leadership are central.</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
