<!-- MEASURED UNIT SIZE -->
<section class="mus-section" id="measured-unit">
<div class="mus-inner">
<div class="mus-left">
<div class="section-eyebrow">Additional factor</div>
<h2>Measured unit size</h2>
<p>Measured Unit Size is an additional factor used to refine the evaluation score for Grid 5 (Impact). It reflects the size of the business unit or organisational context in which the role sits.</p>
<p>This ensures that role size is interpreted in context — because the same role can carry very different weight depending on the size of the environment it operates in.</p>
<p>A Finance Manager in a 50-person business and a Finance Manager in a 5,000-person organisation are not the same role in terms of complexity, accountability, or impact — even if the title is identical.</p>
</div>
<div class="mus-right">
<div style="font-size:12px;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;color:var(--slate);margin-bottom:16px;">Relative role weight by organisational size</div>
<div class="mus-visual">
<div class="mus-bar-row">
