<!-- WHAT ENGAGE EVALUATES / DOES NOT -->
<section class="yesno-section" id="engage-evaluates">
<div class="yesno-inner">
<div class="section-eyebrow">The boundary that matters most</div>
<h2>What Engage evaluates — and what it does not.</h2>
<p>The integrity of any job evaluation system depends on keeping role and person clearly separated. Engage is built to enforce that boundary.</p>
<div class="yesno-grid">
<div class="yesno-col">
<h4 class="yes-head">Engage evaluates</h4>
<ul class="yesno-list">
<li><span class="tick tick-yes">✓</span>The content of the role</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-yes">✓</span>The level of knowledge required</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-yes">✓</span>The complexity of decisions the role makes</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-yes">✓</span>The scale of control and accountability</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-yes">✓</span>The influence and impact of the role</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-yes">✓</span>Where the role sits in the structure</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-yes">✓</span>The size of the operating environment</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="yesno-col">
<h4 class="no-head">Engage does not evaluate</h4>
<ul class="yesno-list">
<li><span class="tick tick-no">✗</span>The current employee's performance</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-no">✗</span>Personal attributes or style</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-no">✗</span>Future ambitions for the role</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-no">✗</span>Proficiency or capability of the incumbent</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-no">✗</span>Market scarcity or retention pressure</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-no">✗</span>Tenure or length of service</li>
<li><span class="tick tick-no">✗</span>What an individual should be paid</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
